Literally one of my favorite easy to make, low sugar, quality protein snacks that’s good for the whole family. Bonus, they’re really pretty and are a great healthy substitute for ice cream 🍦 💗. 
Check out this quick how-to vid. Please LIKE & SAVE to show love. xo 
.
RECIPE:
.
Ingredients

🍓3 tablespoon vanilla lactose free Greek or vegan yogurt
🍓2 teaspoons lime juice
🍓40 grams of sliced strawberries (I prefer using organic strawberries)
Instructions
🍓Measure out the yogurt and add to blender
🍓Measure out the lime juice and add to blender
🍓Blend
🍓Add mix to Popsicle mold 1/4 way up
🍓Add a few sliced strawberries into the mold
🍓Take rest of strawberries, add to blended yogurt mix and BLEND!!!
Pour rest of mix to top of mold, place in freezer to freeze for 24 hours before serving!
.
NUTRITION:

Serving Size: 1 Pop
Calories: 46
Sugar: 6.2
Fat: 0.13
Carbohydrates: 8.3
Fiber: 0.85
Protein: 3.55
.

In honor of Father's Day yesterday, I'm sharing hubs fave drink, fresh-made Water Melon Juice 🍉🍉🍉
Ingredients: Watermelon... (yup, that's it). Personally I like to make it in a good blender. 
To spice it up, put it back in the mini watermelon and slice a bit off the bottom so it can sit on the table without rolling. 
Add an umbrella for pizazz ⛱⛱⛱.. We like to have it as is, but I know a lot of people like to add a splash of alcohol (or more than a splash, lol)... which one are you? Drop a 🍉🍉🍉 in the comments if you prefer just watermelon juice and a 🥂🥂🥂 if you like to take it up a notch. xoxo .
PS... This drink was originally inspired by the QueenB - "I been drinking, watermelon... " - #beyonce 👑🐝
.
PPS ... See hubs on my instastories right now with Tyson for fathers day ❤️
PPPS.. pls like & save to show love. Muah! 😘

HOURGLASS WORKOUT CLOSED BY COVID 19 😪
.
..
... it's hard to say goodbye... 😢❤️... so, instead, we'll say thank you to everyone that's touched the Hourglass Workout’s downtown location in any way over the last 13 years of business... Unfortunately running a 5000sf studio in the heart of downtown Toronto is just not possible to sustain moving toward our 3rd month of shut down with no end in sight for the fitness industry... with over $30K in operational expenses, we've had to make the tough but necessary call to close our doors 😔... so, once again.. thank you to the best of the best instructors, the most amazing clients/ friends and to our family of location owners 🙏🏽.. we love you, we thank you and we say goodbye to this chapter of life... We will continue with our online training, so please join us there (all support is greatly appreciated), but for now... please share your love for Hourglass Downtown below... This is a very tough day all of us, so any love & virtual hugs are appreciated.. (this was our 10 yr anniversary video attached. vids of 2018 on, are on my stories)... Some Hourglass locations are still fighting to remain open 💪🏽🙏🏽. More info to come. 
Hugs.. Lyza & the Hourglass Team
.
.
.

This is one of my favorite blender juice recipes. It’s sweet, spicy and green.. which is why I call it Sweet Spicy Greens. It’s great because you can make it right in your blender. 
When you make a blender juices, here are a few things to keep in mind: 
1. blender juice keeps the fibre that’s removed in traditional juicing, so it’s so filling, that you may not be able to finish. 
2. It’s best to finish the whole juice within 20 minutes of juicing it, as blended juice will not maintain its vitamins, minerals and enzymes the way a cold pressed juice will.

Deadbug is one of my fave exercises for the core, but, to do it effectively, you need to really bring in the mind-muscle connection. Here are a few tips to keep in mind:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
1) Keep your spine in neutral while starting a Pilates zip up (Kegels up, pull lower abs in, drop belly button to spine and pull the ribs together). ⁠⠀
2) Press your legs and hands into the ball like your trying to pop it. ⁠⠀

4) Exhale as you bring them back and push into the ball to activate your core. ⁠⠀
5) Repeat on the other side. ⁠⠀
⁠.
3 sets of 20 total reps (slow and controlled focusing on breathing and connection). ⁠⠀

One of my all time fave recipes, and one of the ones that I make the most to stay on track personally.. ZOODLES!!! Macro-wise.. it's on point to help keep me lean. How does it work? You use zucchini noodles in place of spaghetti noodles. The trick to the dish is really tasty meat sauce. When it's really flavorful, you don't miss the pasta. But.. don't just take my word for it.. here's the full recipe (below) 😎😘⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I include this recipe in my SUGAR CLEANSE (link in bio)- fully macro'ed eating plan, great for the whole family. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
I also include a modified version of the recipe without the tomato (nightshade veggie) in my FlatBellyChallenge 'elimination diet' eating plan for a flat belly and healthy gut! (link also in bio). ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Pls share with someone who would love this recipe 😘⁠⠀
⁠.⠀
.⠀
.⠀
⠀
LYZA'S ZOODLES: ⁠⠀
⁠⠀
INGREDIETS:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
1 organic zucchini – spiral cut½ cup tomato sauce⁠⠀
1 lb lean ground turkey (you can sub lean meat or chicken)⁠⠀
Jalapeño olives⁠⠀
Sliced Button mushrooms⁠⠀
2 tbsp Braggs Aminos⁠⠀
1–2 tbsp Sriracha hot sauce (to taste)⁠⠀
1 tbsp coconut oil⁠⠀
1 small jalapeno (finely chopped)⁠⠀
1 clove garlic (finely chopped)⁠⠀
Instructions⁠⠀
⁠⠀
Cut the ends from each of the zucchini.⁠⠀
Put the zucchini through a zucchini noodle maker (spiralizers can be found at most department stores in kitchen sections)⁠⠀
Heat coconut oil or organic butter, add the zucchini spaghetti, salt, pepper and (dill weed optional).⁠⠀
Quickly saute the zucchini until crisp tender (it will cook fast, in less than 5 minutes).⁠⠀
Taste and adjust the seasonings; serve twirled onto the plate OR Leave zucchini raw, add pinch salt & pepper to taste (add low sugar tomato organic tomato sauce and healthy ground turkey or meatballs!⁠⠀
Meat sauce: Add turkey and begin to break the meat into very small pieces, Add braggs and sriracha hot sauce.⁠⠀
Once the meat is cooked, add tomato sauce, mushrooms, jalapeño olives and stir!⁠⠀
.⠀

One of my all-time fave waist-shrinking exercises!! Listen to the instructions on the vid... but keep in mind, to get the most out of this exercise... you'll want to ensure that you do your Pilates ZIP UP first... ⁠⠀
I do this exercise when I'm doing Pilates, but I also love to throw this and other Pilates exercises in-between sets of weight lifting exercises (as active rest). For example, on a shoulder day, at the end of a super-set of all Shoulder exercises, I'll throw some hundreds in at the end of each set to get some quality abs in while letting my shoulders rest a bit. ⁠⠀
🔑Why I love Pilates: Pilates has helped me to permanently, structurally changed my core. I lost over 2 inches from my ribs all the way to the smallest part of my waist without losing fat or weight in general. I retrained my core for an over-all smaller waistline and better posture... this ish is like magic when you hit the form and do it with consistency ... ✨...⁠⠀
.⁠⠀
😎Want more FlatBelly Tricks... check the link in my bio for my FlatBellyChallenge eating plan... a holistic and healthy way to heal your gut and get you to a flatter belly. 😎..⁠⠀
⁠.⁠⠀
KEYS for the HUNDREDS exercise:⁠⠀
⁠⠀
📍Do not drive your chin forward, keep it in line with your spine⁠⠀
📍Start your Pilates zip up before you begin your reps (pull kegals up, pull your lower abs in, belly button to spine, draw your ribs together) ⁠⠀
📍Do not lift your middle back off the floor, curl your shoulders off the floor lightly and engage your core⁠⠀
📍The arm pump comes from the shoulder hinge, not the elbow or wrist and your torso should NOT move with it. It should only be your arms moving in the pump. ⁠⠀
⁠⠀

This home reno has had us busy!! Hubs and I have not been on a date night in months, so we jumped at the chance to travel back to the city (literally back to the block that we lived on in the Toronto Entertainment District), to enjoy a staycation at one of Toronto’s newest Hot Spots, @1kitchentoronto / @1hotels . This hotel/restaurant focuses on being sustainable from using food from their own backyard garden, to using local furniture makers, and bakeries etc. 
We enjoyed a delicious 5 course sustainable dinner, followed by a sound bath meditation by the roof top pool overlooking the city. 
I haven’t been hitting the gym too much lately with my focus on renos, I’m mainly following my sugar cleanse recipes, but the gym at this hotel was amazing! With Woodway treadmills, and a cross fit style set up, it would make any gym junkie very happy! 
Special thanks to @haloandcompany for giving hubs & I such a wonderful night out with friends in the fitness community. This staycation is 100% recommended!

node.text:
We’ve now officially moved and Tyson who just turned 2 1/2 years old is learning about changes. He adjusted to his new room immediately, but we also prioritized that it was the first room done and had most of the same furniture and his favourite toys. He misses his friends so much and says “no friends” and cries, literally heartbreaking. Luckily he gets to zoom with his friends from downtown Toronto and we’re planning a fun playdate in the next few weeks. We’ve now started his new daycare which has been a blessing. We transferred from the downtown @kidcochildcare to the Kids & Company Childcare in our new area. It’s so handy that they have them all across North America and makes moving or travel much easier for your child. They all have similar programming, food, facility set-up and schedules etc. This is so helpful as it’s one less thing for him to have to adjust to. We’re excited for him to create new friendships as he gets more comfortable there. 
We're adding some art work to the new house and had some pics done by @jessbaumung . We’re going to make them black & white and frame a few. Help us choose which one to use: 1, 2 or 3? 
Thanks guys. HUGS! 
#kidsandco #kidsandcompany #kidsandcopartner #toddler

It was just over a year ago that I was forced to permanently shut down my downtown Toronto Flagship of the Hourglass Workout Gym. After 13 years in business, COVID-19 shut us down. Toronto continues to have the longest lockdown in North America. To date, gyms are still shut down currently and have been for more than a year in total time closed. Today Toronto reported 42 cases of COVID-19 (Toronto population 2.7 million). We also have over 75% with a first vaccine shot and over 30% fully vaccinated, yet gyms remain shut down. 
Fitness is essential and it is key in our mental and physical well being. It’s time make it a priority to find a way to work with gyms to reopen safely and provide financial assistance that actually applies to gym. Gym owners are willing to do whatever it takes. I applaud the gyms that have survived this long in lockdown. It’s time to prioritize the reopening of gyms and supporting the entrepreneurs that put their heart into them. 

I’m curious, where do you live and are your gyms open? 

Tag your favorite gym to let them know your support them. Contact your local government officials to help!! 

#Imisshourglassworkout #savegyms #supportlocal

So, I’ve been on my hair journey working to bring back my natural curls from damage of over-bleaching and heat styling etc.
Regardless of adding less blond to my hair and choosing better hair products, I know I’m still going to want to heat style on occasion, so I’ve been searching for styling products that give a great look with less heat damage.
I found the @farrah_hair ❤️ I love this curling iron as it loosely grabs your hairs with its self-turning both directions iron and gives it a beautiful soft curl right to the tips in one shot without your being snug tight right against the iron. It also gives a really beautiful result. *For this look I used The Farrah for the majority of the style, but also used my flat iron on low heat to smooth areas as needed*
If you’re also looking for beautiful style with less damage, check out the farrah, I’ve linked them in my bio. For a limited time use promo code: LYZA for 20% off. #farrahpartner #ad #thefarrah #farrah_hair

node.text:
Tyson has been so blessed to have best friends. He’s has had friends at the park from before he was even one year old, but when he was placed in the same class at @kidcochildcare daycare as friends from the playground, they soon become a tight knit little baby crew, lol. 
Having a toddler born into a pandemic and living in Toronto (we’ve had the longest stay home order in the entire continent .. and yes, we’re still in a lock down), it’s definitely been tough. But, nothing makes me happier than seeing the three of them run to eachother screaming out eachothers names when they see eachouther at the park after dinner after only being apart for a few hours, lol… literally though! 

There are so many benefits to daycare, but Tyson’s friendships are definitely among my very favorite. Knowing we’re moving soon… moving him away from his daycare, teachers and friends is the one thing that keeps me a bit awake at night. I know he’ll be okay, but it still makes me sad. We’ll be joining another @kidcochildcare when we move so I’m happy he’ll be in a similar environment.. We’ll miss our friends, but we must look forward… Raffy, Kai & Archie (& mama’s and dada’s)… you’ll be missed more than you know. On to the next chapter… xoxox 
.

@jennifermwilliams @jeremylumdanson @vanvounaaa @maggarghaly @seemasahel & Reeshi 
.
#kidsandcopartner #bestfriends #tyson

THERE’S NO MAGIC PILL 💊 
While I do love taking supplements to fill in the gaps, there’s nothing like the power of whole foods. Here are a few of my favorite foods that I keep stacked in the fridge for each macronutrient: 

Fats: Avocados, chia seeds, hemp seeds, wild caught fish and nuts & seeds in the pantry 
.
Carbs: fruits, veggies (fresh & frozen), pre-made organic veggie soups, Kim chi. We buy breads, pastas on some occasions, but they are not regularly stocked. 
.
Protein: bone broth protein, bone broth, frozen/ fresh high quality meats. 
.
**These are the foods that you’ll find in my fridge in most days of the week. I follow the 80/20 rule.. I also keep some dark chocolate, and wine gums in the pantry as well , and indulge in ‘fun foods for cheat meals & special occasions ’ 🤗
.
Do you prefer to keep your fridge stocked, or eat on the go? 😘
